Great Night Out is an upbeat British comedy-drama based in Stockport, North-West England that aired on ITV in early 2013.

The programme follows the lives of four former school friends "Beggsy" William Ash (actor), Paddy Hogkinson "Hodge" (played by Lee Boardman, the geeky character Glynn Thwaite Craig Parkinson and Darren "Daz" Taylor Stephen Walters, who are all fans of Stockport County FC. The characters often end up in scraps with their wives and go to the local pub whose working-class and comical landlord Warren Peterson Ricky Tomlinson puts on quizzes and football games.

The series follows single man Glynn who works for Connor McIntyre "Mad Ton" meets love interest Julie Liverman played by Christine Bottomley, whilst the ups and downs of "Hodge's" relation ship with wife Kath Hodgekinson Rebekah Staton are prominent in the series, along with often hilarious escapades of the four men.
